#GENERAL NOTES
#   1)YOLO is a Deep Neural Network(DNN) that operates from convolution layers. It's backbone(Darknet-53) is a CNN.
#   2) 
#   3)
#YOLO Fundamentals
#1) Everything in YOLO is a tensor(SxSx(B*5 + C))Where S is number of boxes on one side, B is a box with FIVE values, and C is number of classes
#2) Utilized Convolution Neural Network(CNN, AKA the black box) to grab features and patterns(edges, textures, shapes, objects)
#3) Darknet-53 is YOLOv3's backbone(big black box)

#YOLO Pipeline
#1) Grab Input image
#2) Throw it into CNN(Darknet-53)
#3) Use three scales(13X13, 26X26, 52X52) to predict B anchor boxes per grid cell, outputting x,y,w,h values and markers of probabilities for classes
#4) Compile all that data into actual bounding boxes and probabilities(confidence)
#5) Scrap boxes that are not likely to be objects
#6) Get rid of boxes that overlap, and keep just the best one per object
#7) Now you have the frame with just the best boxes and labels